items.title: They did it for Dairy-These People Threw Themselves Down a Hill for Cheese
items.description: In England’s annual homage to chaos disguised as tradition, thrill-seekers hurled themselves down a muddy 200-yard hill chasing a runaway wheel of cheese—because why use stairs when you can risk a concussion? German YouTuber Tom Kopke claimed victory (again), tumbling into first place like a human tumbleweed and proudly clutching his seven-pound prize like it was Olympic gold. Meanwhile, the women’s champ somersaulted her way into fame, bonked her head, and still called it a win. Dressed in morph suits and delusions of glory, competitors once again proved that gravity is undefeated. Broken bones? Likely. Dignity? Not so much. SMH. Read for yourself.

items.title: This A.I. might be making movie scenes that look and sound just like real life - And you might not even notice.
items.description: Just when you thought A.I. was happy sketching cats and writing poems, Google cranked the dial to 11 with Veo 3—a video-making A.I. that can whip up lifelike videos complete with voices, barking dogs, and singing fish. Now, tech junkies can feed it a 'prompt' - (a sentence or two), and get back a full-blown life-like scene. Fooled by a video of 100 dogs doing a synchronized dance in China? Just wait until you’re nodding along to a heartwarming clip of Tom Hanks rescuing a dolphin from a flooded Walmart—only to find out it was cooked up by A.I. with no soul and too much free time. The line between real and ridiculous just got blurrier. SMH. Your heads up below
